  "title": "Production Manager [Food Manufacturing | West]",
  "description": "<p>[Job ID: 1424687]</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage and supervise daily food production operations to ensure efficiency, safety, and quality.</li><li>Oversee production lines and line leaders to ensure smooth and uninterrupted production.</li><li>Coordinate with purchasing, marketing, and sales teams to support production planning.</li><li>Plan and schedule periodic cleaning of production lines.</li><li>Manage monthly stock checks for raw materials and work-in-progress (WIP).</li><li>Oversee proper use and maintenance of production equipment and machinery.</li><li>Ensure all SOPs, WSH risk assessments, SWPs (Safe Work Procedures), and training records are properly maintained and audit-ready.</li><li>Ensure compliance with workplace safety and food safety regulations.</li><li>Support internal and external audits related to food safety and workplace safety standards.</li><li>Promote continuous improvement in safety, quality, and operational processes.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>At least 5 years</strong> of experience in <strong>food manufacturing or food production environments.</strong></li><li>Knowledge of <strong>food production processes, SOPs, and production planning.</strong></li><li>Understanding of inventory control, raw material handling, and basic quality control.</li><li>Familiarity with<strong> food safety systems</strong> such as<strong> FSSC 22000, HACCP, and GMP.</strong></li><li>Familiarity with <strong>workplace safety standards</strong>, including <strong>ISO 45001 or equivalent.</strong></li><li>Understanding of Singapore Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) regulations under MOM and food safety regulations enforced by the Singapore Food Agency (SFA).</li><li><strong>WSQ Food Safety and Workplace Safety certifications</strong> are an added <strong>advantage.</strong></li></ul><p>To Apply, please kindly email your updated resume to cv_estheryip@goodjobcreations.com.sg</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. However, rest assured that all applications will be updated to our resume bank for future opportunities.</p><p>Please kindly refer to the Privacy Policy of Good Job Creations for your reference: https://goodjobcreations.com.sg/en/privacy-policy/</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Yip Yan Wen, Esther</p><p>EA Personnel Reg. no.: R25152371</p><p>EA License no.: 07C5771</p>",
